FAQ

Everything you need to know about WeNow

   Is WeNow compatible with any type of vehicle?

   The WeNowBox must be plugged into the diagnostic socket, which is
   mandatory in Europe for all petrol vehicles since 2002 and all diesel
   vehicles since 2004. Some earlier models also have these sockets. If
   you have an older car, please contact us.

   Where should I plug in the WeNowBox? Is it easy to fit in?

   It usually has to be fitted in under the wheel or next to the
   gearshift, depending on your car’s brand and make. The socket looks
   like a SCART socket. It can be located behind a cover you have to
   remove. Once you’ve done that, it only takes 5 minutes to fit in the
   box. If you need any help, feel free to contact us.

   Do I have to have a smartphone?

   We have two types of boxes: the first one can be connected to your
   phone through Bluetooth, and your phone collects the data at the end of
   each ride. The other box operates independently, through a 3G chip that
   collects data autonomously.

   We have two types of boxes: the first one can be connected to your
   phone through Bluetooth, and your phone collects the data at the end of
   each ride. The other box operates independently, through a 3G chip that
   collects data autonomously.

   We only collect the following data: engine fuel injection data when
   available, speed profile, engine speed profile and the vehicle’s
   identification number (VIN) to know its brand, model and what fuel it
   runs on. WeNow doesn’t track your location, in order to protect your
   personal data and privacy. Our app only requires access to your GPS to
   be able to monitor your altimetry –it doesn’t record your GPS position.

   How can you guarantee that my money will actually be spent to offset
   the amount of CO2 I’ve emitted?

   All the projects we’ve selected meet the highest international
   standards (Gold Standard, Verified Carbon Standard or UN) and we only
   work with the best operators in the voluntary carbon market. Our
   partners provide us high-standard counseling to choose the very best
   projects. All projects have been “approved” by third-party auditors
   (DNV, Bureau Veritas, Environmental Services), they each have their own
   serial number to ensure their traceability and they are “checked” every
   five years at least. They have also been chosen for their social added
   value and their environmental quality, which is above the average of
   most carbon offsetting projects.

